channel.title: CVE Feed for Dell -- Wyse Management Suite
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Dell -- Wyse Management Suite

item.title: CVE-2022-29097|2024-09-16T16:22:41.350Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Dell WMS 3.6.1 and below contains a Path Traversal vulnerability in Device API. A remote attacker could potentially exploit this vulnerability, to gain unauthorized read access to the files stored on the server filesystem, with the privileges of the running web application.

item.title: CVE-2022-33924|2024-09-16T19:40:24.856Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Dell Wyse Management Suite 3.6.1 and below contains an Improper Access control vulnerability with which an attacker with no access to create rules could potentially exploit this vulnerability and create rules.

item.title: CVE-2019-3769|2024-09-16T16:43:16.810Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Dell Wyse Management Suite versions prior to 1.4.1 contain a stored cross-site scripting vulnerability. A remote authenticated malicious user with low privileges could exploit this vulnerability to store malicious payload in the device heartbeat request. When victim users access the submitted data through their browsers, the malicious code gets executed by the web browser in the context of the vulnerable application.

item.title: CVE-2022-33931|2024-09-16T22:29:38.782Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Dell Wyse Management Suite 3.6.1 and below contains an Improper Access control vulnerability in UI. An attacker with no access to Alert Classification page could potentially exploit this vulnerability, leading to the change the alert categories.

item.title: CVE-2022-33930|2024-09-16T20:37:54.123Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Dell Wyse Management Suite 3.6.1 and below contains Information Disclosure in Devices error pages. An attacker could potentially exploit this vulnerability, leading to the disclosure of certain sensitive information. The attacker may be able to use the exposed information to access and further vulnerability research.

item.title: CVE-2022-34365|2024-09-16T16:27:55.738Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: WMS 3.7 contains a Path Traversal Vulnerability in Device API. An attacker could potentially exploit this vulnerability, to gain unauthorized read access to the files stored on the server filesystem, with the privileges of the running web application.

item.title: CVE-2021-36336|2024-09-16T19:24:32.413Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Wyse Management Suite 3.3.1 and below versions contain a deserialization vulnerability that could allow an unauthenticated attacker to execute code on the affected system.

item.title: CVE-2018-11063|2024-09-16T19:57:24.083Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Dell WMS versions 1.1 and prior are impacted by multiple unquoted service path vulnerabilities. Affected software installs multiple services incorrectly by specifying the paths to the service executables without quotes. This could potentially allow a low-privileged local user to execute arbitrary executables with elevated privileges.

item.title: CVE-2021-21587|2024-09-16T17:48:44.545Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Dell Wyse Management Suite versions 3.2 and earlier contain a full path disclosure vulnerability. A local unauthenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability in order to obtain the path of files and folders.

item.title: CVE-2022-29096|2024-09-16T19:09:27.426Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Dell Wyse Management Suite 3.6.1 and below contains a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerability in saveGroupConfigurations page. An authenticated attacker could potentially exploit this vulnerability, leading to the execution of malicious HTML or JavaScript code in a victim user's web browser in the context of the vulnerable web application. Exploitation may lead to information disclosure, session theft, or client-side request forgery.
